":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":135999,"output":8,"totalTokens":136007,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776224518840,"responseId":"req_vrtx_011Ca4s84dq3mr2HDC99Y2SF","__openclaw":{"id":"8f377933","seq":1222}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-telegram-direct-6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:6053576134","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1776224521147,"sessionId":"8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":79648,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776224518327,"childSessions":["agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8d8e1952-016d-4c2d-819c-c3b32e3b45b2","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8bffa95f-1686-4571-a0ed-e69d265eb964"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","lastTo":"telegram:6053576134","lastAccountId":"main_bot","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"lưu ý là không sử dụng token bot, token provider và mcp của tôi nhé"}],"timestamp":1776224518327,"__openclaw":{"id":"a72a15c5","seq":1503},"senderLabel":"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead doesn't want to use the existing bot tokens, provider keys, and MCP configs. Each team should use their own credentials. Let me update the setup files to remove the actual tokens and use only placeholders."},{"type":"text","text":"Dạ rõ Lead! Để em cập nhật lại — bỏ hết token/provider/MCP thực, chỉ giữ placeholder cho từng team tự điền.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q3icggv8lerw_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/setup-openclaw/README.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## 🔐 Credentials cần thiết\n\n1. **AHV API Key** — Liên hệ Lead để lấy\n2. **GitLab Token** — Personal Access Token với quyền `api`, `read_repository`, `write_repository`\n3. **Confluence Token** — Atlassian Cloud API Token\n4. **Stitch API Key** — Từ Stitch dashboard (nếu cần UI generation)\n5. **Telegram Bot Token** — Mỗi agent có bot token riêng (xem file `openclaw.json`)","newText":"## 🔐 Credentials cần thiết (tự tạo cho team)\n\n1. **AHV API Key** — Tạo tài khoản trên https://auto.ahvchat.com → lấy API key riêng\n2. **GitLab Token** — Team Dev/QA tạo Personal Access Token trên GitLab.com với quyền `api`, `read_repository`, `write_repository`\n3. **Confluence Token** — Team BA tạo Atlassian Cloud API Token riêng\n4. **Stitch API Key** — Team Dev đăng ký Stitch.ai để lấy key riêng (nếu cần UI generation)\n5. **Telegram Bot Token** — Mỗi team tự tạo bot riêng qua @BotFather"},{"oldText":"1. **AHV API Key** — Liên hệ Lead để lấy","newText":"## ⚠️ Lưu ý quan trọng\n\n> **KHÔNG dùng chung token của người khác.** Mỗi team tự tạo và quản lý credentials riêng.\n\n| Credential | Ai cần | Cách lấy |\n|---|---|---|\n| AHV API Key | Tất cả team | https://auto.ahvchat.com → Account → API Keys |\n| GitLab Token | Dev + QA | GitLab.com → Settings → Access Tokens |\n| Confluence Token | BA | Atlassian Account → Security → API Tokens |\n| Stitch API Key | Dev | https://stitch.design → Dashboard |\n| Telegram Bot | Mỗi agent | @BotFather trên Telegram |"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":239,"output":676,"totalTokens":83780,"cacheRead":79797,"cacheWrite":3068,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776224518493,"responseId":"062e3c088ba685dac4a65759b100ca37","__openclaw":{"id":"a28c128c","seq":1504}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776224308772,"sessionId":"7e5b8575-7b48-44e9-bac8-6582ff8c14a7","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":43634,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776199558073,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/7e5b8575-7b48-44e9-bac8-6582ff8c14a7.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory retrieval returned `disabled: true` — the heartbeat state file is not accessible. I need to compare the current sessions list against the last known state that was reported in the main session's chat history.\n\nFrom the last 5p report (at 03:22 UTC), the state was:\n- DTLX group (-5168104492): FAILED (500 error)\n- QLHV 5p (cron:ed2d0b5d): running\n- DTLX 5p (cron:6f3323ef): running  \n- Agent Status cron (e7885813): running\n- telegram:direct:6053576134: idle\n\n\n- Now checking the current state at 03:38 UTC to identify any changes. The DTLX group is still FAILED and has been for 22 minutes, while the QLHV 5p session continues running. 38 min)\n- cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p): running ✅ (this very cron session)\n- cron:e7885813 (Agent Status): running (but the specific session id is 8b51b783, from updatedAt 1776222098689 = ~03:01 UTC) — it's been running for ~37 minutes which is unusually long\n- telegram:direct:6053576134: status \"done\" (ended at 1776224336614 = ~03:25 UTC) ✅ - was idle before, now DONE\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): status \"running\" but its last message was from the last report\n\nWait, looking more carefully:\n- telegram:direct:6053576134: **done** (ended at 1776224336614 = ~03:25 UTC). This is new! In the 03:22 UTC report it was \"idle\". Now it's done. But \"done\" means it ended normally.\n\nFor the QLHV group, its updatedAt of 1776224356520 suggests it's still receiving messages, though the group session itself ended back at 1776163783190. The QLHV 5p monitor spawned several subagents including c2d275a5, 63bb70ce, and ba49ac6d, all now done, and it appears to have sent a message at 1776224339349.\n\nThe main change I'm seeing is that the Lead's direct session ended normally at 03:25 UTC. Looking back at the previous report from 03:22, the Lead poll was already idle, and now it's completed, so this is just the natural progression of that session ending normally.\n\nThe real question is whether anything substantive changed: the DTLX group is still in a failed state, the 5p cron monitors are still running, the QLHV group is still active, and the Lead's session transition from idle to done is just routine. The e7885813 cron session has been running for about 37 minutes, which is unusually long, but that's likely just the polling taking time rather than a problem.\n\nLooking at what was reported at 03:22, the DTLX group failure was already marked as known and persistent, so nothing new has emerged on that front. Comparing back to the 03:20 report, both the QLHV and DTLX groups showed the same FAILED state back then too. I need to dig deeper to see if there were any actual changes I might have missed.\n\nThe Agent Status cron session e7885813 is still running from 03:01 UTC, which is unusual for a heartbeat that should complete quickly. Let me look at the most recent update to this session around 03:28 UTC to understand what's happening with it.\n\nThe Agent Status cron seems stuck in a loop—it keeps triggering and then aborting due to timeouts. The session shows it's been running since 03:01 but got aborted at 03:29, which suggests it's cycling through attempts rather than completing successfully. Looking back at the earlier cron session, it shows a single message that timed out, then got aborted at 03:29 UTC. But I'm seeing conflicting data across different sessions with IDs 8b51b783 and 6a8cc690 — one appears to have been aborted, yet the session list shows a different cron ID still running.\n\nLet me focus on what's actually changed: the DTLX group is still failing with that same provider error, the QLHV 5p monitor is continuing normally, and I need to check if the cron session I was tracking has progressed or failed.\n\nLooking at the cron:6f3323ef session that started this report, it appears to be cut off mid-status, but I should verify whether that's still the active running session or if something's shifted.\n\nThe real question is whether anything material has changed since the last report at 03:28 UTC: the DTLX failure is still present, the QLHV 5p monitor continues its normal cycle, the Lead session has finished cleanly, and the Agent Status cron is cycling as expected. Nothing suggests an actual state change, so I should probably stay silent.\n\nWait, I'm noticing the cron:e7885813 session—it's been running for about 37 minutes since 03:01 UTC. If the previous report was at 03:28 UTC and this session was already running then, then it hasn't actually changed state. Let me check the QLHV 5p session to see if there are any other updates.\n\nThe QLHV group session has an updatedAt timestamp from 03:25 UTC, which is more recent than the last message I saw at 03:22 UTC. But looking at the message history, it seems like the QLHV session was already active and responding to messages around 03:17-03:22 UTC, so this isn't necessarily a new change.\n\nActually, checking the timestamps more carefully—the last message in the QLHV session was at 03:25 UTC, and that's the report message I just saw. The updatedAt timestamp of 03:25 UTC suggests this is the same session still running normally, not a fresh reactivation.\n\nSo comparing the state: DTLX group is still FAILED, QLHV 5p monitor is still running, the DTLX 5p cron is still running (that's me), Agent Status cron is still cycling, and the Lead session has moved from idle to done. But the Lead session ending was already reported in the 03:28 UTC report, so that's not new information. The QLHV group session is also still marked as done from 03:22 UTC, so there's no change there either.\n\nThe real issue is that the cron:e7885813 Agent Status session has been running for 37 minutes since 03:01 UTC, which is unusually long for a heartbeat, but I need to check what its updatedAt timestamp actually is to understand if it's genuinely still active or if it's stuck.\n\nLooking at the cron:e7885813 session, its updatedAt is 1776222098689 (around 03:01 UTC), which is the same as when it started—the session appears to be doing nothing, just polling. The e7885813 session itself is a subagent spawned by the cron, and it got aborted at 03:29 UTC.\n\nBut then the cron session itself is still marked as running, so there's a discrepancy here. Let me step back and focus on what actually matters: are there any real changes from the 03:28 UTC report? Looking at the current sessions, the DTLX group is still failing, the QLHV 5p monitor is still running, and the cron:e7885813 is still cycling. Nothing substantive has changed. I'm trying to figure out the timeline here—the QLHV 5p session was reported as \"went from idle to active\" at 03:28 UTC, but the main session heartbeat showed a message at 03:33 UTC about state comparison, which suggests the cron ran again after that point. Let me trace through the timestamps more carefully to see if there's been any meaningful change since the last stable report. So the 5p Monitor cron cycle ran around 03:33 UTC and triggered the agent status check, which then timed out sending to the QLHV group and fell back to the direct message instead. The agent status delivery itself had already been marked as degraded in the 03:20 UTC report, so there's nothing substantively new there.\n\nComparing back to the 03:28 UTC report, the QLHV group going from idle to active was already flagged then, so the timing makes sense. The real issue is whether the Agent Status cron itself is stuck or just taking longer than expected—it was started at 1776222097981, which converts to around 03:01 UTC, and if it's been running for 37 minutes that's unusual for a cron that typically completes quickly.\n\nLooking at the actual task behavior, the Agent Status cron is spawning subagents to check sessions and send messages, which could easily run for 30+ minutes in an active ecosystem, especially if there are failed Telegram sessions to report. So this doesn't necessarily indicate a problem—it's probably just doing real work.\n\nI don't see any state changes from the last report, so I'm staying silent.\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The last DTLX 5p report was at 03:28 UTC showing the QLHV group reactivated, but before that at 03:20 and 03:22 UTC the DTLX group was confirmed failed. At 03:28 UTC there was another report from the other cron session showing QLHV reactivated plus the Agent Status message, and now this cron session is running at 03:38 UTC. Comparing the DTLX-specific sessions, the DTLX ecosystem is still in a FAILED state, the 5p monitor is still running, and there don't appear to be any new changes to report.\n\nThe DTLX ecosystem group failure is persistent and already known, so there's nothing new to flag. I'm going to stay silent."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state against the last known state (from the 03:28 UTC report):\n\n- **DTLX ecosystem group (-5168104492)**: Still FAILED (same `providerSpecificData` 500 error, persisted since 03:16 UTC — already documented)\n- **DTLX 5p Monitor (cron:6f3323ef)**: Still running (this very session)\n- **QLHV 5p Monitor (cron:ed2d0b5d)**: Still running, still active\n- **Agent Status cron (e7885813)**: Still cycling (known abort/recover pattern, already degraded-flagged)\n- **Lead direct session**: Now DONE (ended normally at ~03:25 UTC — was already idle at last report, nothing new)\n\n**No new changes detected. Pipeline state matches prior report.**\n\nStaying silent."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":29263,"output":2261,"totalTokens":45895,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":427,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776224408387,"responseId":"062e3b9930952d6952b72a41c1afb637","__openclaw":{"id":"2c591551","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:main","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat","to":"heartbeat"},"updatedAt":1776223534771,"sessionId":"bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":141989,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776223523955,"endedAt":1776223531375,"runtimeMs":7420,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","lastTo":"heartbeat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/bca9bbb9-d1eb-408d-9e3d-14dd521dcc45.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":623,"output":8,"totalTokens":137759,"cacheRead":137128,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776219460220,"responseId":"req_vrtx_011Ca4khi8B5Dhy4y1Zh3Eps","__openclaw":{"id":"5b2b6e71","seq":173}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-15 02:41:25 UTC] 🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 02:37 UTC 15 Apr\nSystem: \nSystem: Changes detected:\nSystem: • ABORT: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — Reques