and no longer active.\n\nFor the master-orchestrator, I'm noting that the main session ended about 13 minutes ago, the Lead poll is idle with the last activity around 01:00 UTC, and both the QLHV and DTLX group sessions are also idle. There are no active agent subagents currently running, and I should compile this status report for the Lead. I'm checking the session list more carefully to distinguish between cron sessions (which should report as running) and regular sessions that are actually done or idle. The Agent Status cron is this very session, the QLHV 5p Monitor is actively running, the DTLX 5p Monitor is running but started much earlier, and the two orphaned cron sessions are stale and should be excluded.\n\nLooking at the non-cron sessions, all of them show as done or idle with no active work happening right now—just monitoring crons ticking away in the background. I'll format the report for the Lead with the active cron sessions that are actually running, keeping it concise and relevant."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_haidn5llr1bn_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 03:01 UTC 15 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 2\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p Monitor): running — pipeline health check (QLHV ecosystem) — 10m\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p Monitor): running — pipeline health check (DTLX ecosystem) — 55m\n\nIdle/ended sessions: 3\n• cron:ac986a8d: orphaned stale (~12h) — flagged for kill\n• cron:b653a6c0: orphaned stale (~21h) — flagged for kill\n• main: done (last heartbeat 02:17 UTC) ✅\n• telegram:direct:6053576134: idle — last status sent 02:44 UTC — idle 17m\n\nNo active subagents. No current task sessions.\n\nPipeline: ✅ HEALTHY\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: 2× orphaned cron sessions (ac986a8d, b653a6c0) — cleanup pending\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model"